\b \cf0 Overall:
\b0 \
- The unit MUST be connected to Ethernet and be using an external power supply during the tests. (Reason is that Ethernet connection and power from computer may affect noise levels etc. - for instance this has proved to be the case for the T-bar/Slider values)\
- When loading the final sketch, set MAC address and test ATEM connection. Document this on video.\
\

\b For all I2C devices:
\b0 \
- For boards with I2C communication, run the Scanning examples from PCA9685 and/or MCP23017. \
- Check ALL address dip-switch positions; that they report the correct address with the scanning tests\
- For a prolonged amount of time, run the SkaarhojUtils::ChipScanning test to make sure the board addressing works. Problems and crashes over time tends to be due to addressing pins which are floating.\
\
